Serena Willams into fourth round at Australian Open
2012-01-21 12:15:17 GMT
MELBOURNE, Jan. 21 (Xinhua) -- Five-time champion Serena Williams completed another routine two-set win to advance into the fourth round of Australian Open here on Saturday after defeating Greta Arn of Hungary 6-1, 6-1.The 30-year-old American lost just two games and moved a step close to her sixth Australian Open women's singles title. 32-year-old Arn started well and had a chance to break in the opening game, which was as close as she got as Williams stepped up to overpower her opponent and ran away with the match in just 59 minutes.Williams broke Arn twice in the first set and three times in the second to enlarge her unbeaten run at Melbourne park to 17 matches. Williams turns 31 in September but hasn't won a Grand Slam in her 30s. The last champion she won was at Wimbledon in 2010 when she was 28. She hasn't lost in the Rod Laver Arena since the 2008 quarterfinals which beaten by Jelena Jankovic.Next up Williams faces Ekaterina Makarova, who beat fellow Russian and seventh-seeded Vera Zvonareva earlier Saturday.Williams is now the only American left in the singles after Vania King lost to former French Open winner Ana Ivanovic. The last American man exited the tournament is John Isner who lost to Spaniard Feliciano Lopez in five sets on Friday."I'm definitely going to keep representing the flag and doing the best I can," Williams said.
